<emphasis bold="true" box="[309,487,1238,1262]" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">designated here</emphasis>
):— 
<collectingCountry box="[526,617,1238,1262]" name="Egypt" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">EGYPT</collectingCountry>
. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:355D878DFFE70577E886FB53FBF56A3C:B82B6040FFE70577EA7DFB35FD7966D4" box="[627,711,1238,1262]" country="Egypt" municipality="Forsskal" name="Kahirae" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">Káhirae</location>
in desertis, 
<emphasis box="[840,933,1238,1262]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">
<collectingMunicipality box="[840,933,1238,1262]" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">Forsskal</collectingMunicipality>
</emphasis>
692 [barcode 
<specimenCode box="[1087,1217,1238,1262]" collectionCode="C" country="Denmark" name="University of Copenhagen" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" type="Herbarium">C10002396</specimenCode>
], 
<figureCitation box="[1234,1297,1238,1262]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,229,1779,1801]" captionTargetBox="[303,1284,187,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-26@1.[303,1284,187,1752]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lectotype of D. erythraeum [barcode no. C10002396]. [Reproduced with the kind permission of the Natural History Museum of Denmark.]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785891" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785891/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1164,2054]" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">
<bibRefCitation author="Webb, P. B. &amp; Berthelot, S." box="[189,529,1274,1298]" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" refId="ref1519" refString="Webb, P. B. &amp; Berthelot, S. (1848) Histoire Naturelle Iles Canaries tome Troisieme deuxtmeme partie, Phytographia Cannariensis, Sect. III, Bethune, editeur, Paris, 341 pp." type="book" year="1848">Webb and Berthelot (1848: 341)</bibRefCitation>
cited 
<specimenCount box="[592,752,1274,1298]" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
in the protologue. The specimens collected by Forsskal and Delile were mentioned under 
<taxonomicName authority="Forsskal (1775: 209)" authorityName="Forsskal" authorityPageNumber="209" authorityYear="1775" box="[383,838,1310,1334]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Hyacinthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serotinus">
<emphasis box="[383,608,1310,1334]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">Hyacinthus serotinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Forsskal, P." box="[616,838,1310,1334]" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" refId="ref1188" refString="Forsskal, P. (1775) Flora Aegyptiaco-Arabica: sive descriptiones plantarum. Hauniae, Copenhagen, 209 pp." type="book" year="1775">Forsskal (1775: 209)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
whereas those of Weist and Schimper under 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Uropetalum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serotinum">Uropetalum serotinum</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
In the protologue, it was not specified that in which herbarium or institution, the specimens are stored. Forsskal collected the specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forsskal" authorityYear="1775" box="[410,634,1382,1406]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Hyacinthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serotinus">
<emphasis box="[410,634,1382,1406]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">Hyacinthus serotinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingRegion box="[735,808,1382,1406]" country="Egypt" name="Al Qahirah" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">Kahira</collectingRegion>
desert (
<collectingRegion box="[890,952,1382,1406]" country="Egypt" name="Al Qahirah" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">Cairo</collectingRegion>
) in 
<collectingCountry box="[992,1056,1382,1406]" name="Egypt" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">Egypt</collectingCountry>
while he was on a Danish Expedition during 1761-1763 (
<bibRefCitation author="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S." box="[340,590,1418,1442]" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" pagination="616 - 618" refId="ref1308" refString="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S. (1976) Taxonomic literature. A selective guide to botanical publications and collection with dates, commentaries and types, 2 nd ed., 1: A-G. Regnum Vegetabile 1. pp. 616 - 618 &amp; pp. 855 - 857" type="book chapter" year="1976">Stafleu &amp; Cowan 1976</bibRefCitation>
). The expedition lasted for around seven years, six people were appointed for this expedition and Forsskal was one of them. His main task in the expedition was to find evidence for a number of Linnaeus accounts (Rasmussen 2022). There are 
<specimenCount box="[564,724,1490,1514]" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
of Forsskal that are presently available at the Museum Botanicum Hauniense, University of Copenhagen (
<collectionCode box="[556,575,1526,1550]" country="Denmark" name="University of Copenhagen" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" type="Herbarium">C</collectionCode>
) bearing the numbers 692 and 17. Both these specimens have been annotated by P. Ascherson, a German botanist (
<bibRefCitation author="Ascherson, P." box="[465,647,1562,1586]" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" refId="ref1091" refString="Ascherson, P. (1862 - 1876) Correspondence: Ascherson (Paul) and Engelmann (George). Available from: https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 132974  page / 1 / mode / 1 up (Accessed 15 July 2022)" type="url" year="1862">Ascherson, 1862</bibRefCitation>
-1876). In the present investigation, the specimen with field no. 692 [barcode 
<collectionCode box="[136,153,1598,1622]" country="Denmark" name="University of Copenhagen" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" type="Herbarium">C</collectionCode>
10002396] has been chosen as the 
<typeStatus box="[517,615,1598,1622]" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">lectotype</typeStatus>
as this is the only specimen with much of its part preserved. The specimen with field no. 17 [barcode no. 
<collectionCode box="[405,422,1634,1658]" country="Denmark" name="University of Copenhagen" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" type="Herbarium">C</collectionCode>
10002395] remains the 
<typeStatus box="[675,758,1634,1658]" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">syntype</typeStatus>
as the exact dates of collection could not be ascertained.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1164,2054]" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">
Delile, a French botanist, had been to 
<collectingCountry box="[607,671,1670,1694]" name="Egypt" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">Egypt</collectingCountry>
during the expedition of the French army where he made observations, descriptions of plants, which he published individually in Fl. Aegyp. Illustr. in 1813 and also in Description de l’ 
<collectingCountry box="[1342,1420,1706,1730]" name="Egypt" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">Egypte</collectingCountry>
, in 1812 (
<bibRefCitation author="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S." box="[203,455,1742,1766]" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" pagination="616 - 618" refId="ref1308" refString="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S. (1976) Taxonomic literature. A selective guide to botanical publications and collection with dates, commentaries and types, 2 nd ed., 1: A-G. Regnum Vegetabile 1. pp. 616 - 618 &amp; pp. 855 - 857" type="book chapter" year="1976">Stafleu &amp; Cowan 1976</bibRefCitation>
). There are no specimens or illustrations that can be linked to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Webb &amp; Berthelot" authorityYear="1848" box="[1115,1271,1742,1766]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dipcadi" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erythraeum">
<emphasis box="[1115,1271,1742,1766]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">D. erythraeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1164,2054]" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">
Schimper, a German botanist and naturalist and Weist, a Roman botanist, were both travel companions as both were working with Esslinger Botanical Travel Association (based in Esslingen, near Stuttgart, 
<collectingCountry box="[1112,1213,1814,1838]" name="Germany" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">Germany</collectingCountry>
) that existed between 1825-1845 and was to collect, identify and distribute herbarium specimens, seeds, and to a lesser extent minerals and zoological specimens for research work (
<bibRefCitation author="Worz, A." box="[582,708,1886,1910]" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" pagination="171 - 174" refId="ref1558" refString="Worz, A. (2016) Der Esslinger Botanische Reiseverein 1825 - 1845. Logos Verlag, Berlin, pp. 171 - 174." type="book chapter" year="2016">Worz 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Schimper and Weist undertook a research trip to 
<collectingCountry box="[1261,1325,1886,1910]" name="Egypt" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">Egypt</collectingCountry>
and Arabia where they collected 
<taxonomicName box="[368,609,1922,1946]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Uropetalum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serotinum">
<emphasis box="[368,609,1922,1946]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">Uropetalum serotinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 1835 (
<bibRefCitation author="Worz, A." box="[714,839,1922,1946]" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" pagination="171 - 174" refId="ref1558" refString="Worz, A. (2016) Der Esslinger Botanische Reiseverein 1825 - 1845. Logos Verlag, Berlin, pp. 171 - 174." type="book chapter" year="2016">Worz 2016</bibRefCitation>
). We could not locate Weist’s specimen, that might have been destroyed during World War II whereas Schimper’s specimen was discovered in the Central National Herbarium, Botanical Survey of 
<collectingCountry box="[361,418,1994,2018]" name="India" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">India</collectingCountry>
, Kolkata (
<collectionCode box="[532,588,1994,2018]" country="India" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:12692" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:12692" name="Botanical Survey of India" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" type="Herbarium">CAL</collectionCode>
) and bears field no. 405 [barcode no 
<collectionCode box="[1000,1054,1994,2018]" country="India" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:12692" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:12692" name="Botanical Survey of India" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" type="Herbarium">CAL</collectionCode>
0000031365] and the collection year 1835 as mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Webb, P. B. &amp; Berthelot, S." box="[377,653,2030,2054]" pageId="0" pageNumber="274" refId="ref1519" refString="Webb, P. B. &amp; Berthelot, S. (1848) Histoire Naturelle Iles Canaries tome Troisieme deuxtmeme partie, Phytographia Cannariensis, Sect. III, Bethune, editeur, Paris, 341 pp." type="book" year="1848">Webb &amp; Berthelot (1848)</bibRefCitation>
. This specimen is treated here as 
<typeStatus box="[1009,1095,2030,2054]" pageId="0" pageNumber="274">syntype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
